"The alleged damage occurred during the military service of the plaintiffs," the document says.
The Department of Defense denies any comment on this story.
Things have changed since the 1950s.
If women are still not admitted to service in combat, the distinction is only in the name: modern wars rarely have clear fronts.
Both in Iraq and Afghanistan, teams of soldiers are increasingly playing important roles, especially in contact with local women in the war zones.
