Nine laws were introduced independently of each other by a mix of senators and representatives of both parties to Congress, which offer a number of clues.
In 2010, according to the Sexual Assault Prevention and Response Office (i.e. Office for Prevention and Reporting of Sexual Abuse) of the Ministry of Defense, 3,158 sexual abuses were reported.
